			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2011</a> paper:</span><br><i>MoScript: A DSL for Querying and Manipulating Model Repositories</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/WolfgangKling.html">Wolfgang Kling</a>, <a href="../profile/FrédéricJouault.html">Frédéric Jouault</a>, <a href="../profile/DennisWagelaar.html">Dennis Wagelaar</a>, <a href="../profile/MarcoBrambilla.html">Marco Brambilla</a>, <a href="../profile/JordiCabot.html">Jordi Cabot</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-642-28830-2_10">10.1007/978-3-642-28830-2_10</a></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t3c.html"><span class="tagM">T3C: DSLs</span></a><ul><li> MoScript is introduced as a DSL tailored to querying and manipulating model repositories.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t3f.html"><span class="tagL">T3F: API</span></a><ul><li> It provides an interface layer for accessing repository functionality via scripting queries and updates.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4b.html"><span class="tagL">T4B: Horizontal Transformation</span></a><ul><li> Repository queries and updates operationalize transformations over stored models and their representations.
</li></ul></li></ul>
